                <w:sz w:val="22"/>
                <w:szCs w:val="22"/>
              </w:rPr>
              <w:t xml:space="preserve">not exist</w:t>
            </w:r>
            <w:r>
              <w:rPr>
                <w:rFonts w:ascii="Hanken Grotesk" w:cs="Hanken Grotesk" w:eastAsia="Hanken Grotesk" w:hAnsi="Hanken Grotesk"/>
                <w:color w:val="425466"/>
                <w:sz w:val="22"/>
                <w:szCs w:val="22"/>
              </w:rPr>
              <w:t xml:space="preserve"> until the Phillips curve is unlocked. In stages 0 and 1 the economy is Blanchard&#x2019;s core short run: prices are constant, so the real rate equals the nominal rate (r = i), and there is no expected-inflation control. The Fisher line, the real-rate line, and the πᵉ slider all appear together the moment the PC block unlocks at stage 2.</w:t>
